<h2 id="section-top">Gynaecology</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=967">Pennine Acute Hospitals NHS Trust</a>
</p>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div class="service-locations clear">
<div class="panel edit-box">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<p class="address"><br/>0161 624 0420</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContentd0c4c3db17e043ac8b47eca0889801cd">
</div>
<p><strong>The Trust provides gynaecology services at The Royal Oldham (ROH), North Manchester General (NMGH), Fairfield General (FGH) and Rochdale Infirmary (RI).  Acute inpatient services are provided at ROH and NMGH, whereas outpatient and day surgery services are provided closer to where you live.  FGH and RI are the two main sites for providing day surgery.  All outpatient services including ultrasound, early pregnancy unit and diagnostics are provided at the four sites mentioned above.  There is a concentration of specialist services on the two acute sites, ROH and NMGH.</strong></p>
<p><strong>The Trust is centralising services as it believes this is the most efficient and effective way to use staff skills and resources to deliver improved services for its patients.  Changing the way services are delivered will support the ongoing development of sub specialties within the field of gynaecology which are subfertility, cancer services, endometriosis and pelvic pain, menopause, contraception advice including permanent methods eg laparascopic sterilisation and urogynaecology including incontinence and pelvic floor prolapses.  Specialist services are also provided for recurrent miscarriage.</strong></p></div>
</div>
</div>
